<subSubSection pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="56.[189,303,898,924]" box="[189,303,898,924]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,898,924]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,898,924]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="56.[189,1399,944,1287]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
The type specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[460,620,944,970]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albimanus">
<emphasis box="[460,620,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">M. albimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a black fore femur in contrast with the mostly red fore femur of the similar Colombian species 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[583,730,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albipedis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[583,730,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">M. albipedis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[737,830,980,1006]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and they have more extensive red pigmentation of the lower thoracic pleuron (including the katepisternum) and abdominal base compared to 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[189,336,1049,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albipedis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,336,1049,1075]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">M. albipedis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[342,433,1050,1076]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Despite these differences, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[747,908,1049,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albimanus">
<emphasis box="[747,908,1049,1075]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">M. albimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[965,1112,1049,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albipedis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[965,1112,1049,1075]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">M. albipedis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1118,1208,1050,1076]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are very similar and need to be reconsidered once fresh material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[797,960,1085,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albimanus">
<emphasis box="[797,960,1085,1111]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">M. albimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is obtained. The internal genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[189,354,1120,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albimanus">
<emphasis box="[189,354,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">M. albimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have not been examined, but the oviscape of the 
<typeStatus box="[968,1019,1120,1146]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">type</typeStatus>
is relatively bare and shiny, in contrast to the distinctly setulose oviscape of 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[760,912,1155,1181]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albipedis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[760,912,1155,1181]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">M. albipedis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[924,1020,1156,1182]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The two known specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[189,350,1190,1216]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albimanus">
<emphasis box="[189,350,1190,1216]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">M. albimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also differ from 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[549,696,1190,1216]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albipedis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[549,696,1190,1216]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">M. albipedis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[703,793,1191,1217]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having a clearly visible abdominal pleuron, with distinct black triangular bands tapering down from the lateral margins of tergites 3, 4 and 5. The pleuron is not visible on the available specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[701,848,1261,1287]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albipedis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[701,848,1261,1287]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">M. albipedis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[855,945,1261,1287]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
